              <header class="style1">
                <h2>The Top Opioid Affected States: Ohio</h2>
              </header>
              <a href="#" class="image featured"> <img src="../images/ohio01.jpg"

                  alt="picture of ohio"> </a> <br>
              <p><b>Overdose Deaths</b></p>
              <p>In 2015, the state of Ohio had a recorded 3,310 overdoses that
                resulted in death. A wallowing 82% (2,698) of those deaths were
                caused by opioid overdoses. </p>
              <p>A study from 2014 shows that the drug overdose deaths per
                100,000 people in that year was 24.6 compared to the 9.9 in
                2004. This is a huge increase in deaths (roughly 150%) in a
                short 10 year period. Of the 46,000 residents that were admitted
                for substance abuse in 2014, roughly 37% of them required
                treatment for opioids.</p>
            </article>
            <a href="#" class="image featured"> </a> 
            <div class="row 150%"><a href="#" class="image featured"> </a>
              <div class="4u 12u(mobile)">
                <section class="box">
                  <header><br>
                    <h2>Dayton</h2>
                  </header>
                  <a href="#" class="image featured"><img src="../images/ohio02dayton.jpg"

                      alt="Picture of Dayton"></a>
                  <p>In 2016 Dayton, Ohio recorded 270 overdose deaths, the most
                    of all U.S cities in that year.</p>
                </section>
              </div>
              <div class="4u 12u(mobile)">
                <section class="box">
                  <header> <br>
                    <h2>Cincinnati</h2>
                  </header>
                  <a href="#" class="image featured"><img src="../images/ohio03cincinnati.jpg"

                      alt="Picture of Cincinnati"></a>
                  <p>The city of Cincinnati recorded 264 overdose deaths in 2016
                    and was it's most fatal drug year to date.</p>
                </section>
              </div>
              <div class="4u 12u(mobile)">
                <section class="box">
                  <header> <br>
                    <h2>Toledo</h2>
                  </header>
                  <a href="#" class="image featured"><img src="../images/ohio04toledo.jpg"

                      alt="Picture of Toledo"></a>
                  <p>The city of Toledo recorded 122 overdose deaths in 2016.
                    Compared to the city's smaller population, this is a high
                    number of drug related overdoses.</p>
                </section>
